title: Shorthanded Roncalli falls 2-1
text:
Shorthanded Roncalli falls 2-1 HTR Media 8:58 p.m. CDT October 8, 2015 Roncalli’s Justin Gottshall, left, and Green Bay NEW Lutheran’s Sam Gast compete for the ball during the first half of a game at Roncalli Thursday. (Photo: Yi-Chin Lee/HTR Media) 1 CONNECT 1 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
With three players out with injuries the Roncalli boys soccer team was upended by visiting Green Bay NEW Lutheran Thursday 2-1. 
The Blazers scored in the 18th and 60th minutes before a goal by Ben Oberbroeckling found the back of the net for the Jets in the 80th to put the hosts on the board. 
Nick Seidl, forced into action due to injury, made six saves in goal for Roncalli. 
Kewaunee 4, Kiel 2: After taking a 2-1 lead into the half, the host Raiders surrendered three second-half goals in the loss. 
Parker Brack scored in the 25th minute assisted by Zach Zorn while Brack turned into the distributor in the 41st minute when he helped Brandon Zamora find the back of the net. 
Jimmy Hintz made 17 saves for the Raiders who were outshot 21-12. 
Cross country 
Cougar Invite: The Manitowoc Lutheran boys were fourth at the nine-team Campbellsport-hosted invite. 
Leading the Lancers was Noah Melso, who took eighth. 
For the girls, Madie Kutz finished 27th.

Girls swimming 
Plymouth 106, Brillion/Valders/Chilton 74: Sammie Bonick and Alyssa Frank each won and individual event to lead the co-op. 
Bonick took first in the 100 freestyle while Frank won the 50 freestyle. Bonick also picked up a second place finish in the 200 freestyle.

Sheboygan North 106, Kiel 77: Individual victories in four events weren’t enough as the host Raiders were defeated by the Golden Raiders. 
Madison Bushke won the 200 freestyle, Lauren Boos finished first in the 50 freestyle and Mary Tanouye was victorious in the 100 breaststroke in the swimming events. 
Also for the Raiders, Sydney Vian won the diving competition.
